At the same time, the administration moved to constrict independent sources of information. Voice of America, which had historically continued broadcasting through funding lapses, was ordered to suspend all news operations and furlough its journalists. The decision came shortly after a judge had reinstated hundreds of VOA employees in a separate dispute, and it left a major government-funded news outlet silent at a moment of crisis. In the private sphere, Apple removed an app called IceBlock, which allowed users to track ICE activity, after pressure from the administration. The company cited \'93safety risks,\'94 but the timing\'97amid a major immigration crackdown\'97raised questions about whether federal power was being used to shape what tools citizens could use to monitor enforcement. Together with the partisan agency messaging, these moves deepened a pattern in which state-aligned narratives were amplified while independent or critical channels were constrained. Information itself became a terrain of control.\
