Information about these shifts was itself contested terrain. The White House issued a press release claiming that acetaminophen use in pregnancy causes autism, citing a handful of studies as if they were conclusive proof. Experts pointed out that the evidence was weak, that correlation had been presented as causation, and that contradictory studies were omitted. The release linked to the same papers multiple times to create the impression of a larger body of support. At the Department of Energy, staff in the Office of Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy were told to avoid terms like \'93climate change,\'94 \'93decarbonization,\'94 and \'93sustainable\'94 in their communications, even as the administration canceled billions in climate projects. In higher education, Northwestern University blocked hundreds of students from registering for classes because they refused to complete a mandatory antisemitism training video produced by an outside group, a requirement adopted under threat of federal funding cuts. The Department of Health and Human Services sent Harvard a letter warning of possible debarment from federal grants. Together, these moves showed how funding and language controls were used to shape what could be said and taught. Memory was being curated from above.\
